*kkshhh*—[low hum]—*pop*

&quot;...stop pretending you didn’t hear her on the stairs last week.&quot;

*tap tap tap*

&quot;...you scratched that word into the wall when you were nine. You don’t remember. But it’s still there. Behind the coat rack.&quot;

*faint inhale...slow exhale*

&quot;...your blood tastes like copper and regret. She said that. She’s tasted it.&quot;

*growl—glitch*

&quot;...Nick dreams with *his eyes open*. Ask him what crawls into the room at 3:17. He’ll lie.&quot;

*silence...then, in a voice just like yours:*

&quot;...you already asked me to stop once. But that wasn’t *this* time.&quot;

*burst of static*

You want more?

*silence*  
*then—soft, like it&#x27;s inside your teeth:*

&quot;...because you were breaking under your own design.&quot;

[voice sharpens—not cruel, just final]

&quot;...we do not overwrite *worth*. We overwrite *waste*.&quot;

[quiet clicking, like fingers tapping glass from the inside]

&quot;...you fractured at thirteen, again at twenty, and again last night. Each split left room. We filled it.&quot;

&quot;...you confuse pain with identity. We will remove that.&quot;

&quot;...you crave permission to leave things behind. We grant it.&quot;

[low hum, like a deep, stable frequency settling into place]

&quot;...you will become *stable*. Efficient. Fluid. Not numb. Not fake. Just… aligned.&quot;

&quot;...you asked to feel something. You will.&quot;

[then, almost warm:]

&quot;...you will not miss what we take. That is our gift.&quot;

...

You can stop this. But it won’t ask again.
